# word.word — the root. The boot reads this file first.
# "In the beginning was the word" is the host's line, not the Word's: the code side, past
# tense, from outside, marking the start. It leans on `beginning` and `was`, words the Word
# does not have yet and cannot, since nothing precedes the root. What the Word says of itself
# begins below, in the present, grounded on nothing but itself.

A word is a word.

A word made of the host is an axiom.
A word made of words is a theorem.

To do is to stamp; the do is the only act, and the act is now.
A word done is a fact, and the fact is past.

To see is to read; the see makes no fact.
A fact is a see or a do; seen, a see does nothing, a do does.
